# Monorepo Conventions

## Structure

```
rfe-v0/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ apps/          ‚Üê deployable applications
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ rfe-v0/    ‚Üê Next.js + Payload website
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ packages/      ‚Üê shared internal packages
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ design-tokens/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tsconfig/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ eslint-config/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ specs/         ‚Üê spec-driven development docs
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose.yml
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pnpm-workspace.yaml
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ turbo.json
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ package.json   ‚Üê root workspace (no app code)
```

## Package naming

All internal packages use the `@rfe/` scope:

| Package | Name | Purpose |
|---------|------|---------|
| `packages/ui` | `@rfe/ui` | Shared UI components + cn() utility |
| `packages/design-tokens` | `@rfe/design-tokens` | CSS variables, brand colors, easings |
| `packages/tsconfig` | `@rfe/tsconfig` | Shared TypeScript configurations |
| `packages/eslint-config` | `@rfe/eslint-config` | Shared ESLint flat config |
| `apps/rfe-v0` | `@rfe/v0` | The Next.js + Payload website |

## Dependency direction

```
apps/* ‚îÄ‚îÄimports‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∂ packages/*
packages/* ‚îÄ‚îÄNEVER imports‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∂ apps/*
packages/* ‚îÄ‚îÄmay import‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∂ other packages/*
```

- Apps depend on packages, never the reverse
- Packages may depend on other packages (e.g. `@rfe/ui` depends on `@rfe/design-tokens`)
- Use `workspace:*` protocol for internal deps

## Version management ‚Äî pnpm catalog

Shared dependency versions are centralized in `pnpm-workspace.yaml` under `catalog:`.
Individual `package.json` files reference versions with `"catalog:"` instead of hardcoded ranges.

Catalog-managed dependencies:
- `react`, `react-dom`
- `next`
- `typescript`
- `tailwindcss`, `@tailwindcss/postcss`
- `payload`, `@payloadcms/*`
- `sharp`

## Where new code goes

- **App-specific** (routes, content components, CMS schemas, seeds) ‚Üí `apps/rfe-v0/`
- **Reusable across apps** (generic UI, utilities, tokens) ‚Üí `packages/`
- **Specs** ‚Üí `specs/`
- **Cursor config** ‚Üí `.cursor/`

## Build orchestration

Turborepo manages task execution:
- `pnpm build` ‚Äî builds all packages then apps (respects `dependsOn: ["^build"]`)
- `pnpm dev` ‚Äî starts app dev server (persistent, no cache)
- `pnpm lint` / `pnpm typecheck` ‚Äî runs across all workspaces

## Rules

- Do NOT publish packages to npm ‚Äî these are workspace-only
- Do NOT create a new package without a spec in `specs/`
- Do NOT add shared dependencies outside the pnpm catalog
- Do NOT import from `apps/*` in any `packages/*` code
- Keep the root `package.json` free of app-level dependencies
